      "message": "What\u0027s the value in having two counters? Note that trying to count errors by getting a difference between instructionsAcked and instructionsReceived will be cumbersome (for example, I have no idea whether it is possible to plot a rate of such errors).\n\nIt would be more direct and useful to have \u0027instructionsReceived\u0027 and \u0027instructionErrors\u0027 (or something) counters. Where errors can also be parametrized by a kind of an error (if it makes sense). At very least there are 3 kinds: \"FAILED_TO_CONFIGURE\", \"FAILED_TO_ACK\", \"FAILED_TO_REBOOT\".\n\nIt would be great if \u0027configureSwarmingAutoStart\u0027 also learned to return a category of an error (perhaps via error tags, see common/errors in luci-go): error during download, file permission error when installing.\n\nFinally, it may make sense to also have a counter for agent.mp.poll calls, that will act as a \"hearbeat\" for liveness of the MP agent. If there\u0027re no data point in last N minutes, then the agent is dead.",
